      "question": "If the points $A(6, 1)$, $B(8, 2)$, $C(9, 4)$, and $D(p, 3)$ are the vertices of a parallelogram taken in order, find the value of $p$.",
      "answer": "$p = 7$",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Diagonals of a parallelogram bisect each other, meaning their midpoints coincide.",
          "Find the midpoint of diagonal $AC$ and diagonal $BD$.",
          "Equate the midpoints and solve for $p$."
        ],
        "derivation": "\\text{Midpoint of } AC = (\\frac{6+9}{2}, \\frac{1+4}{2}) = (7.5, 2.5) \\\\ \\text{Midpoint of } BD = (\\frac{8+p}{2}, \\frac{2+3}{2}) = (\\frac{8+p}{2}, 2.5) \\\\ \\frac{8+p}{2} = 7.5 \\Rightarrow 8+p = 15 \\Rightarrow p = 7"
      },
